    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >What is <i>Show Guts</i>?</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Show Guts</strong> is a chaotic climbing game where you control a stretchy piece of <strong>omochi</strong> — yes, that soft Japanese rice cake — with <strong>grappling</strong> and an unreasonable dream: reach the heavens before losing your guts.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Climb, swing, and bounce your way through floating present boxes, skyscrapers , and torii gates.  <br>Every fall hurts, every rise feels glorious, and every splat echoes with… sticky determination.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Features</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Stretch. Stick. Struggle.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Feel the chewy physics as your omochi clings to the impossible.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Fall once, lose everything.</strong> <br>Precision and patience are your only ingredients for survival.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Aesthetics of absurdity.</strong> <br>Traditional Japanese vibes meet slapstick chaos.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>New Year in the sky.</strong> <br>Chase the sunrise, find the ultimate <strong>Kagami-mochi</strong> at the top.</p></li></ul>",
